Docker Commands
sudo apt update
sudo apt install docker.io
systemctl status docker
sudo docker pull ubuntu
sudo docker images
sudo docker run -itd -p 80:80 --name=assign1 ubuntu
i = interactive, t = terminal, d= detachmode, -p= port first 80 local machine port, 2nd 80 Container, --name=name of the container ubuntu

You can see the container now
sudo docker ps

Enter into the container
sudo docker exec -it assign1 bash (assign1 is the name of the container, you can also provide container id)

Update the container
apt update

Install apachi2
apt install apache2 -y

Check apache2 running or not
service apache2 status
service apache2 start

Copy the Public ip of the ec2 and paste in the browser with port 80
44.221.48.128:80 (Apache home page will be opened)   


sudo docker images
sudo docker commit assign1 newimage
sudo docker images
sudo docker run -itd -p 81:80 --name-assign2 newimage
sudo docker run -itd -p 81:80 --name=assign2 newimage
sudo docker ps
sudo docker exec -it assign2 bash

Command inside the assign2 container
service apache2 status
service apache2 start

Pull image from docker hub
    1  sudo apt update
    2  sudo apt install docker.io -y
    3  docker --version
    4  systemctl status docker
    5  sudo docker pull kareemrulez/newimage
    6  sudo docker images
    7  sudo docker run -itd -p 80:80 --name=assign3 kareemrulez/newimage
    8  sudo docker ps
    9  sudo docker exec -it assign3 bash





